The driver of the truck which overturned on the N11 sustained serious injuries and was taken to Madadeni Provincial Hospital in KwaZulu-Natal.The Orange Grove truck overturned on the N11 Majuba Pass on Sunday, the Newcastle Advertiser reports.After it overturned, and passersby informed friends of scattered crates, containing milk, juice, and yoghurt, which they helped themselves to.The driver of the truck sustained serious injuries and was taken to Madadeni Provincial Hospital. It is unclear whether the driver was still in the vehicle when the crowd relieved the truck of all of its contents. Caxton News ServiceRead original story on newcastleadvertiser.co.za